sentences.content: This scene narrative allow me to practice describing complex illustrated scene.
The scene is decomposed into simpler subscenes.
These subscenes are identified by overlays with corresponding subscene labels.
These subscenes serve as the bases for sentence fill-in and reading exercises that promote sentence formation.
The subscene narrative fill-ins lets me practice forming sentences that describe a single illustration.
The illustration has overlays of numbered headings that correspond to the subscene descriptions to afford me more structure, if necessary.

sentences.content: The labeled narrative lets me practice reading multiple sentences that describe a single illustration.
The family goes to the park.
The community library is in the background.
A flagpole is sitting in front of the building.
The play area is surrounded by green grass.
The oldest daughter is riding on the swing.
She is wearing pink overalls and matching shoes.
The little girl is going down a blue slide.
She is holding her arms up while sliding.
She is wearing a floral top and purple shorts.
The toddler is climbing the slide ladder.
He is wearing a blue shirt.
His mother is helping him get up the ladder.
She is wearing a lavender top.
